[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;46r\u001b8\u001b[46d"]
[0.001, "o", "\n\u001b[1;48r\u001b[45;1H; This directive controls whether or not and where PHP will output errors,\r"]
[0.031, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;46r\u001b8\u001b[46d"]
[0.000, "o", "\n\u001b[1;48r\u001b[45;1H; notices and warnings too. Error output is very useful during development, but\r"]
[0.027, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;46r\u001b8\u001b[46d"]
[0.001, "o", "\n\u001b[1;48r\u001b[45;1H; it could be very dangerous in production environments. Depending on the code\r"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;46r\u001b8\u001b[46d"]
[0.001, "o", "\n\u001b[1;48r\u001b[45;1H; which is triggering the error, sensitive information could potentially leak\r"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;46r\u001b8\u001b[46d"]
[0.001, "o", "\n\u001b[1;48r\u001b[45;1H; out of your application such as database usernames and passwords or worse.\r"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;46r\u001b8\u001b[46d"]
[0.000, "o", "\n\u001b[1;48r\u001b[45;1H; For production environments, we recommend logging errors rather than\r"]
